## Key Rules Summary

### Unit Testing
- Use naming convention: `[MethodName]_Should[ExpectedBehavior]_When[Condition]`
- Use Test Data Builders for domain objects
- Use NSubstitute for mocks
- No comments in unit tests
- No blank lines between Arrange statements

### Code Style
- React: Use React 19 features, let React Compiler handle optimizations
- C#: Use C# 14 features, minimal APIs, async/await patterns
- TypeScript: Strict typing, no `any` types
- Follow single responsibility principle

